  <answer><![CDATA[<div class="c-page-content">
<p>Enjoy unforgettable views from the Aiguille du Midi cable car in <a data-udi="umb://document/2735e2389f7c411cb3061226ce7548d1" href="/{localLink:umb://document/2735e2389f7c411cb3061226ce7548d1}" title="Chamonix">Chamonix</a> and journey into the Mont Blanc Massif for sensational (and chilly) views. If it's good enough for Cézanne then it's good enough for us – the lake views from Talloires village have inspired artists and poets for centuries. From <a data-udi="umb://document/a9b36e46564a40b9a29646635ec9a1bc" href="/{localLink:umb://document/a9b36e46564a40b9a29646635ec9a1bc}" title="Samoens">Samoëns</a>, journey to “Le Bout du Monde” or in English “the end of the world” that sits within the Sixt-fer-a-Cheval – you’ll be blown away by the views.</p>
</div>]]></answer>
